    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix crash when creating RLC UM entity with invalid parameters\n\n### Summary\nThe `new_rlc_entity_um()` function in the RLC layer could crash or exhibit undefined behavior when called with invalid parameters. The function now properly validates input parameters and exits with an error message instead of continuing with invalid state.\n\nThis fix adds parameter validation to prevent crashes and provides clear error messages for invalid configurations.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/rlc_v2/rlc_entity.c`: Added validation for `sn_field_length` (must be 5 or 10) and non-negative size/timer parameters\n- `openair2/LAYER2/rlc_v2/rlc_entity.c`: Made error handling consistent with AM entity by using `exit(1)` for all error conditions\n- `openair2/LAYER2/rlc_v2/rlc_entity.c`: Removed redundant validation since parameters are now checked at the beginning\n\n### Reproduction\nBefore this fix, calling `new_rlc_entity_um()` with invalid `sn_field_length` values (e.g., 6, 7, 11) or negative size/timer parameters would cause undefined behavior or crashes later in the RLC processing. The function would continue execution with invalid configuration, leading to incorrect sequence number calculations or buffer management issues.\n\nAfter applying this fix, attempting to create an RLC UM entity with invalid parameters will result in a clear error message being logged and the program exiting, preventing crashes and making debugging easier.\n"
}